  "instructions": [
    "Preheat grill to medium‑high heat.",
    "Slice each green pepper into wedges, removing seeds.",
    "In a bowl, mix olive oil, minced garlic, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper.",
    "Brush pepper wedges with the oil mixture, ensuring even coating.",
    "Place peppers on the grill and cook until charred and tender, about 5–6 minutes per side.",
    "While peppers grill, melt shredded cheese in a small microwave‑safe dish for 30 seconds.",
    "Top each charred pepper wedge with melted cheese.",
    "Grill for an additional 1–2 minutes until cheese is bubbly.",
    "Remove from grill, sprinkle with chopped parsley, and serve hot."
  ],
